Position Summary 
The RMNI Ethics & Compliance group administers the Companyâ€™s global ethics and compliance program, including initiatives such as compliance monitoring, training, and investigations; privacy and risk assessments; and third-party due diligence. As an Compliance Analyst, Ethics & Compliance, youâ€™ll be working on the front lines to protect the Company and ensure that RMNI personnel act with integrity in all aspects of our business. In this role, youâ€™ll support a variety of compliance investigations worldwide relating to RMNIâ€™s  Code of Business Conduct and Ethics  and other applicable policies. 
Essential Duties and Responsibilities 
Compliance topics include Anti-Bribery and Corruption (US Foreign Corrupt Practices Act (and various international equivalent legislations), Conflicts of Interest, Business Conduct and Ethics), as well as U.S. Antiboycott, International Trade and Antitrust/Competition Law reporting. As directed by the Corporate Counsel, Ethics & Compliance, the Compliance Analyst, Ethics & Compliance will perform and/or assist with the following duties: 
Prepares due diligence and review of due diligence activity on third parties, and where necessary, mitigates compliance risks identified with third parties. 
Performs analysis and prepares metrics on various compliance issues. 
Supports other projects including developing training or communicating compliance processes across the business. 
Compiles and analyzes compliance training completions, conflicts of interest disclosures, or other key indicators of compliance. 
In conjunction with the Corporate Counsel, Ethics & Compliance, assesses and analyzes the businessâ€™ compliance environment, identifying issues, making recommendations on corrective actions and ensuring those actions are implemented in a timely manner. 
Understands and keeps up to date with Rimini Street business, services and the commercial environment in which it operates in order to assess changing risks and compliance objectives. 
May perform additional duties and responsibilities as assigned. 
